Some 150 Danish schoolchildren aged  between 14 and 16 will leave for holidays this year bearing lollipop, sweets,  balloons and condoms, all part of a free and festive anti-AIDS packs provided  by officials on this island of Fyn.
The Secretariat for the Prevention of Acquired Immune Deficiency Syndrome  of Fyn -- the island where Hans Christian Andersen wrote his tales -- has also  included posters and a tee-shirt saying "Safer Sex" as well as a compact disc  of US singer Bruce Springsteen's hit song from the film on AIDS, "Philadephia."
Since the beginning of the 1980s, 1,428 cases of AIDS have been registered  in Denmark, 1,065 of them leading to death.
